orted: Ibn al-Mubarak, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cA man will continue to have knowledge as long as he is seeking knowledge. If he assumes that he has knowledge, he has become ignorant.\u201d In another narration, it was said, \"For how long will you seek\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35047,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/25\/abu-darda-ilm-jihad\/","url_meta":{"origin":22778,"position":4},"title":"Abu Darda on \u2018Ilm: Seeking knowledge is an act of jihad","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 25, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi al-Hudhayl reported: Abu Darda, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cWhoever does not consider coming and going for the sake of knowledge to be an act of jihad, he has a shortcoming in his mind and his opinion.\u201d Source: Ja\u0304mi\u2019 Baya\u0304n al-\u2018Ilm wa Fad\u0323lih 159 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21964,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/02\/18\/salaf-seeker-ilm-stop-learning\/","url_meta":{"origin":22778,"position":5},"title":"Salaf on Learning: Not befitting seeker of knowledge to stop learning","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 18, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Manadhir reported: I asked Abu 'Amr ibn al-Ala', may Allah have mercy on him, \u201cFor how long is it appropriate for a man to learn?\u201d Abu 'Amr said, \u201cIt is appropriate for him to learn his entire life.\u201d Sufyan ibn 'Uyaynah, may Allah have mercy on him, was asked,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/22778","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=22778"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/22778\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=22778"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=22778"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=22778"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}